;; showcases the various R (rune) literal syntaxes

;; if you just need to capture a single arbitrary codepoint
;; use the single backslash syntax, works on multibyte characters too

\ä¸– say

;; for commonly used characters not available on a keyboard
;; we have the double backslash R literal syntax
;; below we use \\n to represent the newline R

'Line one' \\n app 'Line two' cat say

;; for simple ASCII we can use the decimal value to specify a R
;; using the slash-a(scii) variation

\a126 say

;; and finally, for utf-8 characters, we can specify their value in hex
;; using the slash-u(tf-8) syntax

\uE7958C say
